==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''[[geldhan]]'', whence also Old Frisian ''gelda'', Old Saxon ''geldan'' (Dutch ''[[gelden]]''), Old High German ''[[geltan]]'' (German ''[[gelten]]''), Old Norse ''[[gjalda]]''
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'jieldan/
===Verb===
'''ġieldan''' (class III strong)

# to [[pay]]; to give something in payment or as due
# to [[repay]], to pay back, to [[restore]]
# to [[requite]]; to [[reward]]

===Descendants===
*English [[yield]]

